# Component and Styling Conventions

## Component Structure
- Use JSX (not TypeScript) for all React components
- Follow PascalCase for component names and file names
- Place related components in their own directories with index files when needed
- Use functional components with hooks exclusively

## Styling Standards
- **Primary**: Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- **Utility**: Use [`cn()`](mdc:src/lib/utils.js) helper for conditional classes
- **Theme**: Use CSS variables via `hsl(var(--variable-name))` pattern
- **Component Variants**: Use `class-variance-authority` for component variants

## UI Component Pattern
```jsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

export function MyComponent({ className, variant = "default", ...props }) {
  return (
    <div 
      className={cn(
        "base-classes", 
        variant === "primary" && "variant-classes",
        className
      )} 
      {...props}
    >
      {/* content */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Import Organization
1. React and React-related imports first
2. Third-party library imports
3. Internal components and utilities (using @ alias)
4. Local imports
5. Type imports last (when used)

## shadcn/ui Integration
- UI components are in [`src/components/ui/`](mdc:src/components/ui/)
- Follow shadcn/ui patterns for component composition
- Use Radix UI primitives as base components
- Configure via [`components.json`](mdc:components.json)
